The paper deals with topology control in wireless ad-hoc networks, which is a problem in the field of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also presents a distributed algorithm, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The algorithm involves constructing a spanner, which is a data structure used in graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses transmission errors and fading signal strength, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
